{{Quote|The True Gods decree that life is suffering, and give us pain to demonstrate their truth. Some among our masters seek favor with the True Gods by seeking pain; Domain Shai was legendary for this. They used the Embrace of Pain the way you or I might take a bath. Perhaps they hoped that by punishing themselves, they might avert the punishments of the True Gods. In this, one must suppose they were&hellip;ah, disappointed. Or perhaps—as Domain Shai's detractors like to whisper—they grew to enjoy the pain.|[[Vergere]]|<ref name="The New Jedi Order: Traitor">''[[The New Jedi Order: Traitor]]''</ref>}}
'''Domain Shai''' was a [[Domain]] of the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] [[Warrior caste]]. Members of the domain were known for their devotion and enjoyment of pain, extreme even by the standards of the Yuuzhan Vong.<ref name="Ruin" /> A particularly notable member of Domain Shai was [[Mongei Shai]], who was part of the Yuuzhan Vong scout force that entered [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]]. His [[Death/Legends|death]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Bimmiel/Legends|Bimmiel]] in the exhibition was a source of pride for the Domain.<ref name="Onslaught" />

Another noteworthy member was [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Shedao Shai]], Mongei Shai's grandson, who led the Yuuzhan Vong's [[Battle of Ithor|attack]] on [[Ithor/Legends|Ithor]]. After Shedao's defeat and death, Domain Shai was dishonored.<ref name="Ruin" /> However, one Yuuzhan Vong who apprenticed under Domain Shai was still sent as an [[Assassin/Legends|assassin]] to murder [[Elan]] after her supposed defection.<ref name="Hero's Trial">''[[The New Jedi Order: Agents of Chaos I: Hero's Trial]]''</ref>

{{Stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|The sadomasochistic theology was not planned, and while we tried to pull back on it, not stress it so much (we really wanted it only to be the extra-fanatical Domain Shai-of which Shedao Shai was a part), it took on a life of its own.|Shelly Shapiro|<ref name="Round Robin">[[Star Wars: New Jedi Order Round-Robin Interview|''Star Wars: New Jedi Order'' Round-Robin Interview]]</ref>}}
Domain Shai first appeared in the [[2000]] novel ''[[The New Jedi Order: Dark Tide I: Onslaught]]'' by [[Michael A. Stackpole]].<ref name="Onslaught" />

According [[Del Rey]] Editor at Large [[Shelly Shapiro]] in the ''[[Star Wars: New Jedi Order Round-Robin Interview]]'', the concept of the Yuuzhan Vong's love of pain was originally confined to Domain Shai, but later authors misunderstood and applied it to the entire species.<ref name="Round Robin" />

